<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-02-25T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-02-25T09:00:00-05:00" n="718" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 165.102/857</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-02-25T14:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1916, 2 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3850. Your 2915, February 21, 9 p. m. I have unofficially approached
                                Foreign Office and requested permit. They state that they do not
                                issue actual permits in London but give orders to the Consul General
                                at Rotterdam to issue permit upon the application of shippers when
                                goods reach Rotterdam. They consider that their undertaking not to
                                interfere with shipment of dyes to the United States as expressed in
                                their note of January 28, cabled to the Department in my 3668 of
                                January 31 [29]<note n="1" xml:id="d718fn1">Not printed; see the
                                    Ambassador’s despatch No. 2967, January 31, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_551">p. 551</ref>.</note> is
                                the same as permit.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>